Subject: [PATCH 01/10] feat: replace date inputs with calendar range picker
 showing blocked dates
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- BookingSidebar now uses react-day-picker range picker (Calendar component
  already installed) instead of plain input[type=date] fields
- Blocked dates fetched from DB (next 12 months) in space page and passed
  as props — shown as strikethrough/greyed in the calendar
- Range validation: selecting a range that spans a blocked date shows an
  error toast and resets checkout date
- Calendar auto-closes when a full range is selected
- CTA button text now shows night count: 'Reserve 3 nights'
- Currency passed through from listing.currency so Madrid listings show €
- Pricing breakdown uses listing currency consistently via fmt() helper
- Clear dates button resets the picker
