Subject: [PATCH 02/10] feat: transactional emails + scheduled iCal sync
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

## Transactional emails (Resend)

Rebuilt email.ts with proper HTML templates and named send functions:
- sendBookingConfirmedGuest — branded confirmation with dates, duration,
  total paid, cancellation policy, and a 'View booking' CTA
- sendNewBookingHost — new booking alert with guest name, payout amount,
  special requests, and link to host/bookings
- sendBookingCancelled — handles both guest and host cancellations;
  shows refund amount where applicable; CTA adapts to role
- sendReviewPrompt — post-stay nudge with link to /bookings/:id/review
- sendReviewReceived — star rating + quoted comment notification for hosts
- sendNewMessage — message preview with Reply CTA

All emails use a shared layout() wrapper with WayWork branding header
and footer. Fire-and-forget pattern (non-blocking .catch()) so email
failures never break the booking flow.

### Trigger points wired:
- confirmBooking() action → guest confirmation + host alert (demo mode)
- cancelBooking() action → both parties notified, refund amount included
- hostCancelBooking() action → both parties notified, full refund shown
- Stripe webhook checkout.session.completed → guest + host emails
  (production Stripe path, both Apaleo and standard flows)

## iCal scheduled sync

New GET /api/cron/ical-sync route secured with Bearer token.
Calls existing syncAllIcalFeeds() which handles all active/paused
listings with an icalUrl — deduplicates, clears stale ICAL blocks,
respects future-only constraint.

CRON_SECRET added to env schema (optional — endpoint rejects all
requests if unset).

### Railway setup instructions (in route comments):
  Schedule: 0 */3 * * *  (every 3 hours)
  Command: curl -sf -H 'Authorization: Bearer $CRON_SECRET'     https://waywork-production.up.railway.app/api/cron/ical-sync
