From: WayWork Build <build@waywork.dev>
Date: Mon, 4 May 2026 04:41:54 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 03/10] fix: currency consistency across all price displays

- ListingCardData interface adds optional currency field
- Listing cards now use formatCurrency(price, currency) instead of $
- Map markers and popups pass currency through to createPriceIcon
- toMapListings() propagates currency from card data
- toListingCardData() in search page maps listing.currency
- Search filter price range hint removes hardcoded $ symbols
- 'Under $150' quick link renamed to 'Under 150/day' (currency-neutral)

All prices now render in the listing's actual currency (EUR for Madrid,
USD as default). formatCurrency uses Intl.NumberFormat internally so
locale-aware formatting is handled automatically.
