MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

## Limehome Madrid listings — Work Score differentiation

Rewrote amenity sets across all 5 Limehome samples to produce a
meaningful score spread using the computeWorkScore algorithm:

  Doctor Fleming Team Apartment  ~91  (standing desk, monitor, whiteboard,
                                        conference table, ergonomic chairs x2,
                                        adjustable lamp, AV)
  Delicias Offsite Flat          ~83  (standing desk, large table, webcam,
                                        speaker, ergonomic chair)
  Plaza de Espana Residence      ~68  (window desk, ergo chair, adjustable
                                        light, webcam)
  Quevedo Work Loft              ~58  (desk + ergo chair only, no AV)
  Julian Camarillo Studio        ~45  (desk only, unverified, 290Mbps = 22pts)

Scores now span 45-91 — guests can meaningfully compare and filter.

## Image fixes

Limehome listings: all 5 had unique property images already; fixed
remaining shared photos (Doctor Fleming and Julian Camarillo both used
photo-1505693416388 — replaced with distinct Unsplash IDs).

Generated listings: replaced picsum.photos placeholder URLs with
curated Unsplash photo pools keyed by workspace type (HOME_OFFICE,
PRIVATE_OFFICE, MEETING_ROOM, HYBRID_SPACE, STUDIO) — 12 photos per
pool. buildImages() now takes workspaceType param and uses a
deterministic hash of the slug to pick distinct images per listing.
LOUNGE_PHOTOS pool used for third image in all generated listings.
