 =?UTF-8?q?-complete=20bookings=20+=20review=20prompt=20emails?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

New GET /api/cron/nightly (secured with CRON_SECRET):

1. Finds all CONFIRMED bookings where checkOut < yesterday and marks
   them COMPLETED. This unlocks the review page gate which checks
   status === COMPLETED before showing the review form.

2. For each newly-completed booking, sends sendReviewPrompt() email
   to the guest (if they have no review yet). Email links directly
   to /bookings/:id/review.

The booking detail page already shows an inline 'Leave Review' CTA
for COMPLETED bookings without a review — this cron wires the same
trigger via email.

Railway setup: 0 3 * * * (3 AM daily)
Same CRON_SECRET as ical-sync — one env var for all cron jobs.
---
